<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-A79BBB14-8F14-4790-A7F4-30D204C55A0A" version="2" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-A79BBB14-8F14-4790-A7F4-30D204C55A0A" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Installation wizard (Part 2) (upto R4.3)</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="M148553-B105"><p class="- topic/p ">The installation wizard starts when the printer is connected to the network and switched on for the first time at customer site. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">It allows you to configure the printer for integration in the customer’s environment. This document describes part 2 of the wizard after the reboot. 
</p><note class="- topic/note " id="GUID-DC0E4A40-44D7-46D8-8593-BD9667A41746"><p class="- topic/p ">The installation wizard cannot be started manually. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Use the settings editor to change these settings if necessary after the installation wizard has finished. 
</p></note><note class="- topic/note " id="GUID-8EA6C5AD-12D9-45B4-87EE-071AC8428DEF"><p class="- topic/p ">You need to install a license file to complete the printer installation. 
</p></note></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Installation</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-D04FE361-B34A-4779-B5A6-17C4C1A38F67" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Part 2 : After the reboot</title><table id="GUID-71D42BED-DEC2-4CDE-B1CF-4C322E9DBA89" pgwide="1" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" align="left" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" align="left" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="90*" align="left" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">System Administrator password setup: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The default value for System Administrator password is 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">71617000</b>. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If the customer insists on setting his own System Administrator password during the printer installation, he can do it now. This is not recommended since you need this password later in the installation procedure. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The password change can also be done with Settings Editor (Configuration &gt; Users &gt; System Administrator &gt; Edit), after the printer installation completed. This is preferred. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If the password has changed or not tap Next. 
</p><fig id="GUID-583B4954-4382-45FB-8B72-0696FCE95C48" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-135C2677-1182-49E5-BBF8-A9791633CC15-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-135C2677-1182-49E5-BBF8-A9791633CC15-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">System Administrator e-mail address setup: 
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Type in the e-mail address. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Tap Next. 
</p></li></ol><fig id="GUID-A65D21AB-5F74-4E23-B7BF-B726591EBDDD" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-BC2CB159-E10C-4855-8690-52F13DDCACA9-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-BC2CB159-E10C-4855-8690-52F13DDCACA9-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Mail server setup: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Configuring a mail server is needed for the System Administrator password recovery. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If the System Administrator forgets his password he can than recover it himself if this setup has been done.(see the User Guide for detailed information): 
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Enter all the mail server settings. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Use the scroll bar to see all available settings. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Tap Next. 
</p></li></ol><fig id="GUID-3F60A74F-5A19-44BD-B611-F317D74FF90B" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-81BD221B-73AF-434D-B962-3CD391D7E78C-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-81BD221B-73AF-434D-B962-3CD391D7E78C-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The connection to the mail server and the mail settings are then tested. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Click OK. 
</p></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remote Service setup: 
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Enable / disable Remote Service. 
</p><note id="GUID-7E46BBD1-EE6D-4705-973A-BCB0956DCD24" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">If updating on-line the embedded TSM via Robin is required, Remote Services must be enabled. 
</p></note></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Enable / disable automatic software upgrades. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Type in the SOID of the organization that sold the machine. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See 
<xref keyref="FAQDOIS001" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-611135E7-18E3-4468-8484-4FA6FE396EBE.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text What to do when you do not know the SOID?>What to do when you do not know the SOID</xref> 
</p><note id="GUID-7A6EE7FC-160F-4B79-82BA-BC933B40B6E7" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">The SOID number must be entered without hyphen (for instance, if the SOID is 0001-0001, type in 00010001) 
</p></note></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Type in the verification code. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Tap Next. 
</p></li></ol><fig id="GUID-720B1C80-54D7-4BDF-B598-97AC9E8A44EE" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-E314E754-1C24-44D7-AFFB-A1220E9DC467-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E314E754-1C24-44D7-AFFB-A1220E9DC467-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The connection to the Remote Service server is then tested. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Tap Next. 
</p><fig id="GUID-2B831F84-EE35-4A1C-97C4-1DF674604F17" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-50E07CE1-AD31-4CB2-A06D-BFE85210B912-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-50E07CE1-AD31-4CB2-A06D-BFE85210B912-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">System measurement unit selection: 
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Tap the System of measurement button. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Select the desired unit type from the drop down list. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Tap Next. 
</p></li></ol><fig id="GUID-B9A600C7-23CB-41E5-8DC4-3E75FF7BA953" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-A6B22D92-CA1C-4AD3-8505-CA648850246B-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A6B22D92-CA1C-4AD3-8505-CA648850246B-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">8 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">End of wizard: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Tap Finish to close the installation wizard. 
</p><fig id="GUID-F417B061-67EA-4683-8193-90CDE89BC317" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-B0B7D222-838E-4F12-9155-58F3770A6EBB-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-B0B7D222-838E-4F12-9155-58F3770A6EBB-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">9 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">If Remote Services was enabled in step 5 and updating the embedded TSM via Robin is required, reboot the printer now. 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-7D3F358C-1AB9-4A5D-9B0E-C75D689F152E.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Installation</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</task>